headline: 3 Reasons WST is Risky and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: West Pharmaceutical Services’s 34.6% return over the past six months has outpaced the S&P 500 by 20.2%, and its stock price has climbed to $284.57 per share. This was partly thanks to its solid quarterly results, and the performance may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
